{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017723,"pPcc":"SAT#P","questionId":"8462b105","skill_cd":"P.C.","score_band_range_cd":6,"skill_desc":"Nonlinear functions","createDate":1755117017723,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Advanced Math","ibn":"","external_id":"bb4ceae0-91ef-4a7e-8a48-9eecde3713f6","primary_class_cd":"P","uId":"4d4f8566-c1e9-451c-963e-48a275064948","difficulty":"H"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"mcq","stem":"<p>The function <math alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi>\n</math> gives the product of a number, <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math>, and a number that is <math alttext=\"91\"><mn>91</mn>\n</math> more than <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math>. Which equation defines <math alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi>\n</math>?</p>","keys":["c28a22d6-801c-4866-8ff6-b4a2e74f2345"],"answerOptions":[{"id":"ba04729c-c806-4381-aa44-f17e5dc7f3f7","content":"<p><math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x squared plus x plus 91\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>91</mn></mrow></math></p>"},{"id":"16b6711f-0226-4f87-9737-ca27fa61998b","content":"<p><math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x squared plus 91\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>91</mn></mrow></math></p>"},{"id":"c28a22d6-801c-4866-8ff6-b4a2e74f2345","content":"<p><math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x squared plus 91 x\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>91</mn></mrow><mi>x</mi></math></p>"},{"id":"f138ad75-0733-406e-8d64-c5c586923853","content":"<p><math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x squared plus 91 x plus 91\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>91</mn></mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mrow><mn>91</mn></mrow></math></p>"}],"rationale":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice C is correct. It&rsquo;s given that the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi></math> gives the product of a number, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math>, and a number that is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"91\"><mn>91</mn></math> more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math>. A number that is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"91\"><mn>91</mn></math> more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> can be represented by the expression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus 91\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>91</mn></math>. Therefore, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi></math> can be defined by the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x left parenthesis x plus 91 right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>91</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals x squared plus 91 x\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>91</mn><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>","externalid":"bb4ceae0-91ef-4a7e-8a48-9eecde3713f6","correct_answer":["C"]}}